|  INTRODUCTION  | 
|                | 
 ---------------- 
When I worked for Hokkaidou University from 2010 to 2021, I guided many 
bus excursions.  This file is made based on my excursion notes at the 
time.  (by T. Nihei)
	Place names are written as they are pronounced, for example, 
Hokkaido --> Hokkaidou.  This is because this file is for oral 
explanation (Nihei lab 2025).  #1  #2

NOTE
 
#1  Some place names are displayed in UTF codes.  To convert UTF codes 
to characters on a terminal emulator, use this command;
	echo $'\u5317\u7ADC'

#2  To convert characters to UTF codes on a terminal emulator, use this 
command;
	printf 'CHARACTERS' | iconv -t UTF-16LE | od -t x2 -An -v | \
	tr '[a-z]' '[A-Z]' | sed 's/ /_\\u/g' | sed 's/\\u_//g' | \
	sed 's/\\u$//g' | sed 's/\_//g'

ACKNOWLEDGMENTS

I would like to dedicate this work to Baron Kondou (Kijuurou Kondou) 
who died in 2023.  He studied equitation science in England and 
thoroughbred breeding in our laboratory. He told us interesting stories 
about the old life in Sapporo.
