tidal waves. The tidal waves killed 1,467 people in the Matsumae 
Domain and 566 people in the Tsugaru Domain.  (During the Edo era, the 
Matsumae Domain ruled the south of Hokkaidou Prefecture.  The Tsugaru 
Domain ruled the west of Aomori Prefecture.)
	Tourists cannot land Ooshima island and Kojima island.  
Shelters for fishing boats only exist in these islands. These islands 
are breeding grounds of seabirds such as Umigarasu (murre) and 
Oomizunagi-dori (Streaked shearwater).

#2  As for the Tsugaru Strait, the distance between the Matsumae 
Peninsula and Tsugaru Peninsula (Aomori Prefectrue) is 19.5 kilometers. 
It is the distance between Cape Shirakami in Matsumae Town and Cape 
Tappi-zaki in Sotogahama Town. 
	The distance between the Kameda Peninsula and the Shimokita 
Peninsula (Aomori Prefectrue) is 19.0 kilometers.  It is the distance 
between Cape Shiokubi in the former Toi Town (now Hakodate City) and 
Cape Ooma in Ooma Town.
