``tsuna-shirazu (rope, no need).''  They also called it Tomoe Port 
(spiral port) due to the spiral-like topography.
	The Japan-US Treaty of Peace and Amity (Nichi-bei-washin-
jouyaku) was concluded in 1854.  It was concluded between the Tokugawa 
Shogunate and the United States.  The Port of Hakodate and the Port of 
Shimoda were opened.  (Shimoda is located in the Izu Peninsula, 
Shizuoka Prefecture).
	(The name ``Japan'' is English.  In Japanese, it is called 
''Nihon.''  Therefore, the name ``the Sea of Japan'' is 100 percent 
English.) 
