aged 18 to 19 is high.  This is because there is Tokyo University of 
Science Oshamanbe Campus.  Students come in April and leave in 
February.
	The Oshamanbe campus opened in 1987.  It was during the bubble 
economy.  Baby boomers sustain the Japanese economy and their children 
(2nd baby boomers) would enter universities.
	* * *
	Looking at the map of population density in the country, 
Hokkaidou looks like a black continent (HTTP://MOOO.COM/NOTE/
INTF1.JPG).  This means that Hokkaidou has a very low population 
density.  Today, most people live in and around large cities.
